refinedev/refine#6720.body:
### Describe the bug

The Hasura DataProvider doesn't respect idType when creating subscriptions.


### Steps To Reproduce

1. Pass idType to Hasura data provider:
```
const hasuraDataProvider = dataProvider(client, {
  idType: 'String',
});
```
2. Use useOne hook:
```
const { data, isLoading } = useOne<ThingDto>({
  resource: ResourceType.THING,
  id,
  meta: {
    gqlQuery: THINGS_GET_QUERY,
  },
  queryOptions: getPlainToInstanceOptions(ThingDto, true),
});
```
3. Look at gql websocket subscription messages when loading page:
```
{"id":"...","type":"subscribe","payload":{"query":"
            subscription Things_by_pk($id: uuid!) {
                Things_by_pk(id: $id) ...}}}
```

[I also found the cause.](https://github.com/refinedev/refine/blob/cf44ff9a6c78bfd1a940a1ff50819033d766abdb/packages/hasura/src/utils/generateUseOneSubscription.ts#L32)



### Expected behavior

The subscription should use the idType for the resource rather than use uuid.

### Packages

- @refinedev/hasura 6.6.10

